The probability that a single drug has at most 8 successes is \(P(X \leq 8)\). This is found by computing the complement:
\[
P(X \leq 8) = 1 - P(X = 9) - P(X = 10)
\]
where:
\[
P(X = 10) = (0.7)^{10} = 0.0282475249
\]
\[
P(X = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3) = 10 \times (0.7)^9 \times 0.3 = 10 \times 0.040353607 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821
