\]
\[
P(X \leq 8) = 1 - 0.1493083459 = 0.8506916541
\]

For three independent drugs, the probability that all have at most 8 successes is:
\[
[P(X \leq 8)]^3 = (0.8506916541)^3 \approx 0.615625
\]
The probability that the maximum exceeds eight is the complement:
\[
P(\max > 8) = 1 - 0.615625 = 0.384375
\]
Rounded to three decimal places, this is 0.384.

