Solution: The problem requires finding \( P(Y_7 < 27.3) \), where \( Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8 \) are the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \( \pi_{0.7} = 27.3 \). This means \( P(X_i < 27.3) = 0.7 \) for each observation \( X_i \).

The event \( Y_7 < 27.3 \) occurs if at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than 27.3. Since the observations are independent, the number of observations less than 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with parameters \( n = 8 \) and \( p = 0.7 \).

Thus,  
\[ P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(B \geq 7) = P(B = 7) + P(B = 8), \]  
where \( B \) is binomial(8, 0.7).

Calculate:  
\[ P(B = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3, \]  
\[ (0.7)^7 = 0.0823543, \]  
\[ 8 \times 0.0823543 = 0.6588344, \]  
\[ 0.6588344 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032. \]

\[ P(B = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = 1 \times (0.7)^8 \times 1 = (0.7)^8, \]  
\[ (0.7)^8 = 0.05764801. \]

Sum:  
\[ P(B \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833. \]

Rounding to three significant figures, the result is 0.255.

Summary: The final answer is 0.255
